Lance


Tears streamed down her face as my fingers clasped like a vice around her throat, she was lying on the ground and in shock.

"I'll bring you back, ok? I promise - I'll bring you back." I whispered to her.

She nodded quickly, her blue eyes glistened and stared back at me as I cut off her oxygen, willing her to pass out quickly. The man behind me let out a slow wail of pain as he clutched at his stomach, blood oozing through his fingers, a shard of metal wedged into his abdomen.

As her consciousness faded, her hands came up to mine, but didn't try and stop me. Rather, she clasped them tightly for comfort as her heart slowed and stopped.

